The Pacific Stock Exchange said itwill close one half hour early at 1300, pacific daylight time,due to heavy volume and to coincide with the closing of otherU.S. exchanges.    The exchange closed a half hour early yesterday as well, asboth traders and computers had difficulty keeping up withorders.    A stock exchange spokeswoman said at 1145, pdt the latestestimate on volume at the exchange was 9,147,000 shares.    Yesterday the exchange traded a record volume of over 17mln shares. Reuter&#3;